# DSGVO & GDPR Compliance

Apply these checks whenever features touch personal data, storage, or external services.

## External services

- Confirm whether personal data (including IP) is transferred.
- Verify AVV/DPA and transfer safeguards (for example SCC) where needed.
- Ensure disclosure in Datenschutzerklaerung.

## Storage and consent

- Non-essential cookies/storage require prior consent (TTDSG 25).
- Document cookie/storage name, purpose, category, and retention.
- Gate non-essential behavior behind consent checks.

## Assets and scripts

- Self-host fonts and assets where feasible.
- Do not embed third-party scripts without consent gating.
- Prefer local bundling over external CDNs by default.

## Data minimization

- Collect only required data.
- Define deletion/export strategy where applicable.
- Do not log personal data without explicit justification.

## Risk handling

- If full compliance is disproportionately expensive, document risk and request explicit approval before implementation.
